    "13. What can you do to save a programme from crashing if it encounters an error?\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    #code block\n",
    "except:\n",
    "    pass"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "6cf7d7b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "14. What is the purpose of the try clause? What is the purpose of the except clause?\n",
    "\n",
    "The try clause is used to enclose the code that might raise an exception.\n",
    "The except clause is used to specify how to handle a particular type of exception that occurs within the associated try block. If an exception occurs in the try block, the program doesn't crash"
   ]
  }
